  "closed_reason" : "Not suitable for this site",
  "title" : "Is there a Java continuous testing plugin for Maven?",
  "body" : "<p>I'm looking for a plugin that would run in a console continuously to scan a Maven project's test sources directory, and when it detects a change kicks off a test cycle. Something analogous to <code>mvn scala:cc</code> or the Scala Build Tool, but for Java. Can anyone point me towards one?</p>\n"
